# SUPERSEDED by patches/wine/027-win32u-input-cross-thread-async.patch
#
# Patch 026 wrapped cross-thread set_focus_window / set_active_window
# `send_message` calls in `send_message_timeout(..., SMTO_NORMAL, 2000, FALSE)`
# to break the JUCE-popup-close deadlock where the previous-foreground
# owner thread is stuck mid-C++-destructor. It worked but left the
# sender stalled for ~16s per popup interaction (8 cross-thread sends ×
# 2 s each) — user-perceived as a hang.
#
# Patch 027 replaces those sites with `send_focus_message_async()`, a
# helper that uses `NtUserMessageCall(..., NtUserSendNotifyMessage, FALSE)`
# for cross-thread sends (matching wine's own `set_foreground_window`
# pattern and real Windows behaviour). Sender returns immediately;
# receiver processes the message in its own pump as ISMEX_NOTIFY.
#
# Patch 027 includes a fallback to 026's 2 s send_message_timeout
# path, gated by env var `WINE_VSTPOC_SYNC_FOCUS=1`, so 026's behaviour
# is still available for emergency rollback without a wine rebuild.
#
# Do NOT apply this patch standalone — apply 027 instead.
